e, purify; <span class='sdata'>tanme retaḥ pitā</span> <span class='sdata'>vṛṃktāmityasyaitannidarśanaṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ms. 9. 20.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>4</strong> To turn away, avert. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>5</strong> To remove, set aside. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>6</strong> To give, bestow. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>7</strong> To hurt, injure, kill. <br/> <span style='font-size:larger;font-weight:bold;'>III.</span> 1 <span>P.</span>, 10 <span>U.</span> (<span class='sdata'>varjati, varjayati-te, varjita</span>) <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>1</strong> To shun, avoid. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>2</strong> To give up, abandon. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>3</strong> To exclude, set aside, leave out, except; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ś. 6. 27.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>4</strong> To abstain from. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>5</strong> To cut to pieces. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>6</strong> To take away, deprive (one) of. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>7</strong> To discharge, pour or give out, emit. (The following verse from &nbsp;<span class='ls'>K.R.</span>&nbsp; illustrates the root in its different conjugations: <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>—</strong> <span class='sdata'>vṛṇakti vṛjinaiḥ</span> <span class='sdata'>saṃgaṃ vṛkte ca vṛṣalaiḥ saha . varjatyanārjavopetaiḥ sa</span> <span class='sdata'>varjayati durjanaiḥ ..</span>).","evidence":{"band":3,"band_label":"common -- recognise","rank_all":3583,"count_all":152,"first_era":"Vedic","genre":null,"example":{"sa":"varjanīya","ru":"должны быть оставлены","work":"02_ramayana-ayodhyakanda","passage":"105.39","kind":"translation","source":"corpus_lexicon.jsonl (pwg_ru Phase 4, SanskritLexicography